Practical No :- 2

Adding a user:
User is a person/computer who uses the network,computer services
Its take or work on the machine permission which are read,write,execute by the command
In one system a user can me added in group or individually 
Command:-
 $sudo adduser <username>
 Example:-$sudo adduser Tanmay
 
Network settings:
In this setting or conncetion it usually shows the network conncetion to the devices in the form of 
IP address,Lan,Wan etc.
Command:$sudo ip addr

Configuring services:
This services mainly run in background
It is also know as demon for example smbd,nmbd
Comand :$sudo nano /etc/dhcp/dhcpd.conf

List of services running:
use to find current activites running in background
command:$sudo systemctl

Service Name:isc-dhcp-server.service 

Command to enable a service:
$sudo systemctl enable <service_name>
 Eg: $sudo systemctl enable isc-dhcp-server.service 
 
Command to start a service:                  
$sudo systemctl start <service_name>
   Eg: $sudo systemctl start isc-dhcp-server.service	

 Command to check the status of a service:    
 $sudo systemctl status <service_name>
    Eg: $sudo systemctl status isc-dhcp-server.service
 
 Command to stop a service:                   
 $sudo systemctl stop <service_name> 
   Eg: $sudo systemctl stop isc-dhcp-server.service 
  
Command to auto-start a service:
$sudo systemctl restart <service_name>
   Eg: $sudo systemctl restart isc-dhcp-server.service
